ble insights into the lives of Lewis and Clark and the world of Jeffersonian America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aExplorerszWest (U.S.)vCorrespondence. 7aTravel / United States / West / General.2bisacsh1 aDavies, Phillip L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRonda, James P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014908140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300149081423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300149081/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles